content.description: New route not yet in the guidebooks!  Let us know if you know anything about this one please.  Bouldery start for this one.  The moves are easy once you find them.  Follow the line of bolts up the arete.  Crux is down low and easy climbing above.  Stay to the left for more of a challenge.
content.location: Between Fee Fi Fo Fum and Rapunzel's Revenge.  Climb the Arete, lower from the chains.

content.description:
Shares an anchor with The Blind Prince. This line is a bit steeper and feels a bit more strenous than its neighbor. The crux is pulling over a small bulge. 

  This is a good route for someone starting to break into the 5.10s. Short but secure.
content.location: can start at the same spot as The Blind Prince next to a small cave, but heads right to the first bolt.

content.description: Currently the easiest route on the Rapunzel Wall, and the easiest route on this side of the Tower. The first move is making a strong pull onto the undercut bottom of the cliff. The rest is low-angle climbing.
content.location: The climb to the right of Rapunzel's Revenge.

content.description: A nice scoop with opportunities for stemming as well as the usual pocketed climbing.
content.location: A prominent black streak located just behind a large juniper.

content.description: Vertical climbing up a streak on the wall. Very similar to the other climbs in this area without much that stands out. Still fun climbing.
A short and steep line starting just to the right of a small cave. Stemming moves help ease the climb.

Rapunzel Wall is sort of located to the right of, and in the shadow of, the Enchanted Tower. Tucked back in there, the wall features a few nice moderate routes on vertical to just less than vertical rock. As expected, this a popular place and you may encounter groups of climbers here.
